For a given rate measured at the surface, there is an ambiguity between the exponential depth distribution of emitters ({\it i.e. $\lambda$} ) and the surface density ($\rho_{\lambda}$) that can account for the measured rate. We illustrate this via two examples: in Fig.~\ref{fig:AlfaSurfaceEffectVsLambda} we show the ratio of the surface rate to the rate for constant  bulk contamination 
